    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-31T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6215/24: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-31T23:00:00+03:00"
                            >January 31, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 31—8:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>199. Embassy’s 652, September 29, 5 p.m. 1939<note n="30" xml:id="d125fn30">Not
                        printed; but see telegram No. 1472, September 29, 1939, from The Chargé in
                        Germany, <ref target="frus1939v01#pg_481">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 481</ref>.</note> A communiqué published
                    in today’s newspapers announces the exchange yesterday by Molotov and the German
                        Ambassador<note n="31" xml:id="d125fn31">Friedrich Werner, Count von der
                        Schulenburg.</note> of the instruments of ratification of the agreement
                    concerning juridical relations along the frontier signed August 31, 1940 and of
                    the “protocols and other documents <pb facs="0141" n="129" xml:id="pg_129"/>
                    relating to this agreement”, adding that the agreement is based on the treaty of
                    September 28, 1939 concerning friendship and the boundary between the Soviet
                    Union and Germany,<note n="32" xml:id="d125fn32">Signed in Moscow; for text, see
                            <hi rend="italic">Nazi-Soviet Relations, 1939–1941</hi>, p. 105; or <hi
                            rend="italic">Documents on German Foreign Policy, 1918–1945</hi>, Series
                        D, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">viii</hi>, p. 164.</note> and that it was
                    ratified by the Soviet and German Governments December 5, 1940, on which date it
                    entered into effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
